cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the security of embedded accelerators and neural network models against hardware and software Trojans.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper focuses on the robustness of DL-based models and proposes a collaborative attack framework against neural networks.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is relevant as the paper tests the attack framework on image classification and face recognition tasks.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the deployment of neural network models and the potential harm of inserting software Trojans.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the safety-critical applications of DL-based models, such as intelligent surveillance and autonomous driving.
